{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, however, each molecular category showed variable morphological features represented by FAB classification, except categories with acute promyelocytic leukemia (M3) or AMKL (M7) phenotypes.",
    "Likewise, complex karyotypes, which also define AML-MR 9, were frequently observed in MNX1, HOXr and PICALM::MLLT10 categories.",
    "In NPM1; NPM1 fusion or mutations (76) NUP98r; NUP98 rearrangements (71) UBTF; UBTF tandem duplications (50) CEBPA; CEBPA biallelic or bZIP domain mutations (49) GLISr; GLIS family rearrangements (28) DEK::NUP214 (16) ETS family; FET x ETS rearrangements retaining ETS domains (16) BCL11B; BCL11B structural variants and outlier expression (13) MECOM; MECOM structural variants and outlier expression (10) RBM15::MRTFA (10) PICALM::MLLT10 (8) KAT6Ar; KAT6A rearrangements (7) MNX1; MNX1 structural variants and outlier expression (5) APL; APL with fusions involving RARA or RARB (4)",
    "RUNX1::RUNX1T1-like; RUNX1::CBFA2T2-3 fusions (3)",
    "Group 2: de ining in the absence of Group1"
  ]
}